<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy - Woof & Wander</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container mt-5">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-8 offset-md-2">
                <div class="card shadow-lg">
                    <div class="card-header bg-secondary text-white text-center">
                        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="lead">
                            At <strong>Woof & Wander</strong>, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting
                            your personal information. This policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your
                            data.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="mt-4">Information We Collect</h3>
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                                <i class="bi bi-envelope"></i> <strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email, and
                                other details you provide when registering for an account.
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                                <i class="bi bi-chat-left-dots"></i> <strong>Community Activity:</strong> Posts,
                                comments, and photos shared within the forum and event galleries.
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                                <i class="bi bi-bar-chart-fill"></i> <strong>Event Data:</strong> Location and
                                attendance information for meet-ups you participate in.
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="mt-4">How We Use Your Information</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>To create and manage your account within the platform.</li>
                            <li>To allow you to participate in events, forums, and photo galleries.</li>
                            <li>To send you updates about events and community activities.</li>
                            <li>To improve our services and provide a better user experience.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="mt-4">How We Protect Your Data</h3>
                        <p>
                            We take appropriate measures to ensure your personal information is secure and protected
                            from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. Your data will never be shared with third
                            parties without your explicit consent.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="mt-4">Your Rights</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Access and update your personal information at any time.</li>
                            <li>Request the deletion of your data from our system.</li>
                            <li>Control the visibility of your posts and uploaded photos.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="mt-4">Contact Us</h3>
                        <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this policy, please reach out to us at <a
                                href="mailto:support@woofandwander.com">support@woofandwander.com</a>.</p>

                        <div class="text-center mt-4">
                            <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index">Back to Home</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
